sections.text: 01|Title IV-D case defined.Effective:March 22, 2001Latest Legislation:Senate Bill 180 - 123rd General AssemblyPDF:Download Authenticated PDFAs used in this chapter, "Title IV-D case" means any case in which the child support enforcement agency is enforcing the child support order pursuant to Title IV-D of the "Social Security Act," 88 Stat. 2351 (1975), 42 U.S.C. 651, as amended.
